heaviest_rainfall.status: 23.86mm of rain was recorded as having fallen today, marking an exceptional precipitation event and it ranked 7th out of our records.  A rate of 8.3mm per hour was recorded during the 31.0 hour long storm.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 27.6mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 2nd from our records.  The precipitation lasted 2.6 hours and dumped 6.1mm in total.  A torrential downpour occurred on 02 September 2025 when the rain reached a maximum intensity of 34.3mm per hour.  This happened during a 15.0 hour storm when 21.19mm of rain fell.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 31.0 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 23.86mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
